## Basic Matrix Environments

LaTeX provides six standard matrix environments through the `amsmath` package, each with different delimiters:

### Matrix Environment Overview

<CodeGroup>
```latex all-matrix-types.tex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\begin{document}

% Parentheses matrix (most common)
$\begin{pmatrix}
a & b \\
c & d
\end{pmatrix}$

% Square bracket matrix
$\begin{bmatrix}
1 & 2 & 3 \\
4 & 5 & 6 \\
7 & 8 & 9
\end{bmatrix}$

% Curly brace matrix
$\begin{Bmatrix}
x_1 \\
x_2 \\
x_3
\end{Bmatrix}$

% Determinant (vertical bars)
$\begin{vmatrix}
a & b \\
c & d
\end{vmatrix} = ad - bc$

% Norm (double vertical bars)
$\begin{Vmatrix}
\mathbf{v}
\end{Vmatrix} = \begin{Vmatrix}
1 & 2 \\
3 & 4
\end{Vmatrix}$

% No delimiters
$\begin{matrix}
a & b \\
c & d
\end{matrix}$

\end{document}
```
</CodeGroup>

