| `|` | — | Vertical line between columns |
| `@{text}` | — | Custom separator (replaces default spacing) |
| `*{n}{spec}` | — | Repeat specifier n times |

## Block Matrices

Block matrices are used to partition large matrices into smaller submatrices:

### Basic Block Matrices

<CodeGroup>
```latex block-matrices.tex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\begin{document}

% Simple 2×2 block matrix
$M = \begin{pmatrix}
A & B \\
C & D
\end{pmatrix}$

% With array for lines
$\left[\begin{array}{c|c}
A & B \\
\hline
C & D
\end{array}\right]$

% Detailed block matrix
$\begin{pmatrix}
\begin{matrix}
a_{11} & a_{12} \\
a_{21} & a_{22}
\end{matrix} & 
\begin{matrix}
b_{11} & b_{12} \\
b_{21} & b_{22}
\end{matrix} \\[1em]
\begin{matrix}
c_{11} & c_{12} \\
c_{21} & c_{22}
\end{matrix} & 
\begin{matrix}
d_{11} & d_{12} \\
d_{21} & d_{22}
\end{matrix}
\end{pmatrix}$

% Mixed size blocks
$\begin{pmatrix}
A_{2 \times 2} & \mathbf{b}_{2 \times 1} \\
\mathbf{c}_{1 \times 2} & d_{1 \times 1}
\end{pmatrix}
= 
\begin{pmatrix}
\begin{matrix}
a & b \\
c & d
\end{matrix} & \begin{matrix} e \\ f \end{matrix} \\[0.5em]
\begin{matrix} g & h \end{matrix} & i
\end{pmatrix}$

\end{document}
```
